In the last years JavaScript has become one of the most important programming languages. Probably one of the most famous words related to JavaScript is AJAX (Asynchronous JavaScript and XML).  Request from JavaScript are made through the XmlHttpRequest JavaScript object which lets you open connections, send the request and handle data returned by the server.  This post is about XMLHttpRequest object, how to use it and how to handle data in a synchronous or asynchronous way. function createXHRObject() {
	var xhrobject = null;
	for ( var i = 0; i < XMLHttpFactories.length; i++) {
		try {
			xhrobject = XMLHttpFactoriesi;
		} catch (e) {
			continue;
		}
		break;
	}
	return xhrobject;
}; var req = createXHRObject();
